  "texts": [
    "To address this challenge, a revised version of this model known as GATv2 has been proposed.",
    "In GATv2, attention weights are computed using the following relation (Brody et al. 2021):",
    "Instead of considering the entire neighborhood of each node, GraphSAGE utilizes the sampled neighborhood.",
    "This approach involves randomly selecting a subset of neighbors for each node during the aggregation step.",
    "In this way, GraphSAGE can effectively scale to large graphs while still capturing the local information necessary for node embedding generation."
  ]
}